Package: NLPstudio
Title: Parallel NLP Tools for Processing SEC Filings, Corpus Management, Topic Modeling, and Other Perks
Version: 0.9.3
Authors@R: c(
    person("Francesco", "Grossetti", , "francesco.grossetti@unibocconi.it", 
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5130-7745")))
Description: NLPstudio provides a streamlined and high-performance workflow for working with
  structured and unstructured textual data, particularly SEC EDGAR filings. The package supports
  corpus creation from JSON, tokenization, parsing, singularization, and document-level summarization
  via quanteda, all with parallel backend support through the parallel package. In addition,
  NLPstudio includes tools for computing readability, similarity, and distance measures using
  quanteda.textstats. The package also provides a unified topic-modeling API across text2vec,
  topicmodels, seededlda, and topicmodels.etm, with standardized document-topic weights (DTW),
  topic-word weights (TWW), representative-candidate extraction, generic prediction for new documents,
  and visualization helpers. A model-evaluation and selection layer provides engine-agnostic quality
  metrics, topic-stability diagnostics, topic summaries, and automated grid search over candidate
  topic counts. NLPstudio supports export-ready wide
  and long formats and includes curated domain dictionaries for financial text analysis.
  Built on data.table, quanteda, and parallel, NLPstudio is intended for scalable text analysis in an
  academic context with a particular focus on accounting and finance research domains.
